	Fails to Meet:
2.5-3.49%

The project has major flaws in its MLA formatting.
	Meets Expectations: 
3.5-4.49%

The project has minor flaws in its MLA formatting.
	Exceeds Expectations: 
4.50-5%

The project is perfectly formatted according to MLA guidelines.

Delivery: Project Guidelines

5% 	Radically Fails to meet: 
0-2.49%

The project fails to meet minimum length requirements or exceeds length requirements by 10-20+% of total word count(Ex. On a 1000 word assignment, being 800 words or less or 1200 words or more). 

The project is not of the correct genre (e.g., providing a historical analysis when a rhetorical analysis is called for).	Fails to Meet:
2.5-3.49%

The project fails to meet the minimum or exceeds the maximum length requirements by a total of 10% or less. 
 
The project is of an incorrect but closely related genre, e.g., turning in a project that persuades people to take a stance on the presence of wolves in Yellowstone when the description calls for persuading people to visit Yellowstone.	Meets Expectations:
3.5-4.49%

The project stays within the minimum and maximum length requirements. 

The project is of the correct genre but fails to use the mechanics of its genre in multiple major ways.	Exceeds Expectations:
4.50-5%

The project stays within the minimum and maximum length requirements. 

The piece uses the tools (mechanics) of the genre to its full potential. 


